OL,3,CMeet the Welsh popstar using her music
OL,4,Cto highlight misogyny in the industry
OL,6,F"I think that my music is like looking
OL,7,Fat the social landscape and sort of
OL,8,Fhow I relate to that. And being a
OL,9,Fwoman in the music industry is very
OL,10,Fdifficult. These structures are very
OL,11,Fmuch still in place and I've been in
OL,12,Fso many scenarios where that is so
OL,13,Fhighlighted that I just feel like what
OL,14,Felse do I write about when I feel so
OL,15,Fstrongly about this."
OL,17,FThe recent 'Misogyny in Music' report
OL,18,Ffrom the Women And Equalities
OL,19,FCommission found misogyny in the music
OL,20,Findustry 'endemic' and described it as
OL,21,Fa "boys' club."
